content.description: Start up a small recess or dihedral to the right of the main corner in the center of the wall. This leads to a splitter crack. Once the crack start to squeeze down you’ll see two bolts on the face. Take them through a roof to the anchor.
content.location: To the right of the main dihedral in the center of the wall.

content.description: start up the main dihedral in the center of the wall. the first few moves a bit tough and awkward but well worth it to get to the huge roof above! Past the first few moves the corner cleans up, getting a jam one or two before establishing yourself under the massive roof. Plug a piece and head out left into the 4's roof crack until its apex. Past the roof! these moves are as good as they get!! Continue up the dihedral to a brand new set of anchors!
T pinnacle sits behind Owl Rock and is south facing. It has 4 trad routes all about 70 ft in height.
